            "answer_text": "That was always the thing about Freddie. He would always give 200% every time he stepped on any stage. He constantly pushed for more and more his vision of good music. Music that could bring the masses together, and he had the personality and stage presence to back it up. As energetic of a performance as he strove to put on, he\u2019s still human and he\u2019s gonna sweat, he\u2019s gonna be short of breath, but the one thing he didn\u2019t stop doing was making the fans in the crowd feel as though they were a part of it all. Of course they were tired too. A gigantic crowd that had been there for hours, they\u2019re bound to be. He made them feel important, and not just a passing \u201cYou guys are amazing!\u201d comment, but a physically and vocally engaging set. The rest of the band were tired as well, but were dumbfounded as to why he was so adamant on doing what he was doing, and how he made it look so easy controlling every single person in this huge arena, but he did it. To this day, it\u2019s lauded as one of the best live shows of any musician in rock music history. ",
